WHAT TO AVOID:
Do not create simplistic three-tier systems where you describe one thing per tier and move on. The world is MESSY — there are in-between tiers, exceptions, black market alternatives, cultural variations.
Do not make the technology feel clean and Apple-like. This is cyberpunk. Even the nice tech has problems. Even the elite tier has trade-offs.
Do not ignore the IMMIGRANT QUARTERS — the food, fashion, and daily life of Germantown, Little France, the Arab Quarter, New Lagos, and Little Seoul should be woven throughout, not ghettoized into a sidebar.
Do not describe things in round numbers. Not "3 options" — chaotic, overlapping, competing options. The world is oversaturated with products the way our world is.
